The main focus of this paper will be the 20.7k simulation described in Romé et al. (2022). The 20.7k simulation differs from CTRL_LGM only by the addition of a constant meltwater discharge corresponding to the 20.7 ka BP slice of GLAC-1D meltwater history derived by the protocol introduced in Romé et al. (2022). For each time step of the GLAC-1D ice sheet reconstruction, freshwater discharge was computed from changes in ice sheet elevation at each grid cell and routed to an ocean grid cell using an offline drainage map of the last glacial maximum (Ivanovic et al. 2016). Surface freshwater saturation (i.e. a grid cell salinity of \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
